I have been thinking about perception over a digital screen and sexual preferences last few days after that Lizzo Dance thing. I am calling it the Tiny Woman on Screen Effect.

I think that people like chunkier or more grossly shaped women when viewing things but feel differently when they see them in real life. When we see people on screens we resize them in our imaginations because we assume they are not 1:1 as they are on the screen. So when we see obese women I think we resize them subconsciously to our preferences rather than as they would be accurately. We take cues from the images of large butts or breasts and assume it's what we would like as large, ignoring the blubber as much as possible. When we meet obese women in real life we are already using our cognito-perception to make their faces unique and remember them rather than distort their bodies and so we hold a different standard.

tldr: Lisso is a fat and ugly. Your Waifu could be as well.
